bug.short_desc: ScrollBars could take the wrong size

long_desc.thetext:
I discovered a strange behavior with the scrollbars on a tree for example. If the height of the tree is about the hight needed by the widget, the scrollbars appear and knob is shown really small. This looks like the scrolling area is higher than it really is.
You can easily reproduce the behavior using the feedreader. Just resize the browser window until the folders of the tree are about as high as the tree itself. Maybe you need to try a bit to get the right point. The following screenshot shows how it looks like.
Created attachment 654 Wrong scroll bar knob size.

While this a minor issue, it can be quite irritating to the user (typically there are proportional sliders throughout the framework).
to Johnny.
